    "created_at": "2019-01-18T20:39:07Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-01-18T20:39:07Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I believe tornado on py3 uses the asyncio loop by default, and if you're on py 3.7 then asyncio will automatically use different contexts for different tasks. And probably each cell execution counts as a different task as far as tornado/aio is concerned.\r\n\r\nSounds like the kernel should be explicitly holding a `Context` object and reusing it for each cell execution, instead of letting tornado/aio set the `Context` implicitly."
  },
